<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="688" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d688">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.77/87.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="italic">U. S. S. Petrel</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Puerto Cortés</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Government officer arrived February 6th to seize railroad. I have
                            informed the appointed Government superintendent that I should not
                            permit seizure. Without instructions from Department or Minister, I will
                            enforce this decision. I believe it will not be necessary to use
                            force.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dismukes</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>